      {
        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Solutions_2009s_page_001_8",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Write k(x) = f(x)g(x)h(x); then k' = 6k + 6 and k(0) = 1. One solution for this differential equation with this initial condition is k(x) = tan(6x + n/4); by standard uniqueness, this must necessarily hold for x in some open interval around 0. Now the first given equation becomes",
        "bbox": [
          0.12781954002757723,
          0.5391865081546998,
          0.49060151260400175,
          0.6238722937217629
        ],
        "order": 14
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0005",
