      {
        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Solutions_2009s_page_001_21",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Since p and q are relatively prime, and p divides 5q, we must have p|5, so p = 1 or p = 5. On the other hand, p - q and q are also relatively prime, so p- q divides 5 as well, and p - q must be 1 or $5. This leads to eight possibilities for (p,q): (1,0), (5,0), (5, 10), (1, -4), (1,2), (1,6), (5,4), (5,6). The first three are impossible, while the final five lead to 5n + 2 = 16, -20, -36, 16, -36 respectively, none of which holds for integral n.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5563909772366713,
          0.6046511633519812,
          0.9210526389119592,
          0.7326388890979123
        ],
        "order": 16
      }
    ]
  },
